pc:TextEquiv.pc:Unicode: 2 Which of all our friends, to save us,
Could or would have shed his blood1
But this Saviour died to have us
3 When He lived on earth abased,
Friend of sinners was His name;
4 O! for grace our hearts to soften,
Teach us, Lord, at length to love:
What a Friend we have above.
135 P. 624 DUNBAR. S. MI. M. - B. 924
Comes to me G'er and o'er,
Nearer my parting hour am I
Nearer the throne where Jesus reign,-
Leaving my cross of heavy grief,
Rolling its cold, dark waves between
Me and the world of light.
